  {
    "type": "EXPOSITORY (ENGLISH BIBLE)",
    "name": "Gill's Exposition of the Entire Bible",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": "And the rulers knew not whither I went, or what I did..... The rulers of the city of Jerusalem, who seem to be officers of the king of Persia, since they are distinguished from Jewish rulers in the next clause: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "neither had I as yet told it to the Jews; what he came about and designed to do: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "nor to the priests, nor to the nobles, nor to the rulers; the principal men among the Jews, both ecclesiastical and civil: ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "p",
        "class": "",
        "text": "nor to the rest that did the work; of building and repairing; neither those that were employed in it, nor those that overlooked it. ",
        "children": [
