  {
    "type": "EXEGETICAL (ORIGINAL LANGUAGES)",
    "name": "Pulpit Commentary",
    "elements": [
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_sub_title",
        "text": "Verse 16.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " - ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The rulers",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": ". On Nehemiah's arrival at Jerusalem he found no single individual exercising authority, but a number of persons, a sort of town-council, whom he calls ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "khorim",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " and ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "accented",
        "text": "saganim.",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " It is not clear that he made his commission known to them at first, or indeed that he divulged it before the interview mentioned in vers. 17 and 18. ",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "cmt_word",
        "text": "The rest that did the work",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "",
        "text": " This seems to be said by anticipation, and to mean those who subsequently built the wall. Nehemiah 2:16",
        "children": []
      },
      {
        "element": "span",
        "class": "verse-link",
        "text": "",
        "children": []
      }
